  "prompt": "Can peppermint oil keep mice away?",
  "response": "Yes, peppermint oil can help to repel mice. The strong scent of peppermint is believed to be overwhelming and unpleasant for mice, which may encourage them to avoid areas where the scent is present. To use peppermint oil for this purpose, you can soak cotton balls in the oil and place them strategically around places where mice are likely to enter, such as near entry points, corners, and cabinets. While this method can be helpful, it may not provide a complete solution for a mouse infestation, and it is often recommended to use it in conjunction with other pest control measures.",
